        "WATER MEADOW": "A meadow, or piece of low, flat land, capable of being kept ina state of fertility by being overflowed with water from someadjoining river or stream.",
        "WATER MEASURE": "A measure formerly used for articles brought by water, ascoals, oysters, etc. The water-measure bushel was three gallonslarger than the Winchester bushel. Cowell.",
        "WATER MEASURER": "Any one of numerous species of water; the skater. See Skater,n., 2.",
