        "WATER TORCH": "The common cat-tail (Typha latifolia), the spike of which makesa good torch soaked in oil. Dr. Prior.",
        "WATER TOWER": "A large metal pipe made to be extended vertically by sections,and used for discharging water upon burning buildings.",
        "WATER TREE": "A climbing shrub (Tetracera alnifolia, or potatoria) of WesternAfrica, which pours out a watery sap from the freshly cut stems.",
