        "WHARF": "The bank of a river, or the shore of the sea. [Obs.] \"The fatweed that roots itself in ease on Lethe wharf.\" Shak. Wharf boat, akind of boat moored at the bank of a river, and used for a wharf, inplaces where the height of the water is so variable that a fixedwharf would be useless. [U. S.] Bartlett.-- Wharf rat. (Zoöl.) (a) The common brown rat. (b) A neglected boywho lives around the wharfs. [Slang]",
