        "WHATEVER": "Anything soever which; the thing or things of any kind; beingthis or that; of one nature or another; one thing or another;anything that may be; all that; the whole that; all particulars that;-- used both substantively and adjectively.Whatever fortune stays from his word. Shak.Whatever Earth, all-bearing mother, yields. Milton.Whatever be its intrinsic value. J. H. Newman.",
