        "WHILE": "To cause to pass away pleasantly or without irksomeness ordisgust; to spend or pass; -- usually followed by away.The lovely lady whiled the hours away. Longfellow.",
        "WHILERE": "A little while ago; recently; just now; erewhile. [Obs.]Helpeth me now as I did you whilere. Chaucer.He who, with all heaven's heraldry, whilere Entered the world.Milton.",
