        "WHINE": "To utter a plaintive cry, as some animals; to mean with achildish noise; to complain, or to tell of sorrow, distress, or thelike, in a plaintive, nasal tone; hence, to complain or to beg in amean, unmanly way; to moan basely. \"Whining plovers.\" Spenser.The hounds were . . . staying their coming, but with a whiningaccent, craving liberty. Sir P. Sidney.Dost thou come here to whine Shak.",
