        "WHINGE": "To whine. [Scot.] Burns.",
        "WHINGER": "A kind of hanger or sword used as a knife at meals and as aweapon. [Scot. & Prov. Eng.]The chief acknowledged that he had corrected her with his whinger.Sir W. Scott.",
